QUICK‑START GUIDE — SAM UEI, ENTITY ROLES, AND SYSTEM ACCOUNT
(last updated June 27, 2025)

--------------------------------------------------------------------
1.  OBTAIN A UNIQUE ENTITY ID (UEI)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
• Sign in at SAM.gov with any Login.gov username and password.
• Top banner: choose  "Get Started"  then  "Register Entity"  then
  "Start Registration".
• Complete the wizard:
    – Legal Business Name (must match IRS records exactly)
    – Taxpayer ID Number / EIN (sole proprietors may use SSN)
    – Physical & mailing address
    – At least one NAICS code and (optionally) PSC codes
    – EFT banking information (routing and account numbers)
• Submit the form.  A UEI is issued immediately on the confirmation
  screen.  If you do not already have a CAGE code, Defense Logistics
  Agency assigns one automatically in three to five business days.
• The person who submits the registration is automatically granted
  the “Entity Administrator” role for that UEI.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.  CONFIRM WHETHER A SAM LOGIN IS LINKED TO A UEI
--------------------------------------------------------------------
• Sign in and click the “Workspace” icon (small grid ▦).
• Open  My Roles.
    – If a table titled  “Entity Roles”  appears, you are linked;
      each row shows the UEI, entity name, and your role.
    – If the page reads  “You do not have any entity roles”,
      the login is NOT yet linked to any UEI.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
3.  LINK A USER ACCOUNT TO THE UEI
--------------------------------------------------------------------
A) Administrator invitation  (fastest)
   1. Entity Administrator:  Workspace ➜ Entity Management ➜ (UEI)
      ➜ User Management ➜ Invite User.
   2. Enter coworker’s Login.gov e‑mail address.
   3. Choose role  “Viewer”  (read‑only) or  “Data Entry”.
   4. Click  Send Invite.  Coworker clicks the e‑mail link or accepts
      under  Workspace ➜ Pending Entity Invites.

B) Self‑request  (fallback if admin is unavailable)
   1. User searches  Search ➜ Entities  for the company UEI.
   2. Click  Request Entity Role  and select  Viewer  or  Data Entry.
   3. An Entity Administrator receives a task to approve or deny.

RESULT:  As soon as ANY entity role appears under  My Roles,
         the personal API key’s quota jumps from 10 calls/day
         to 1,000 calls/day.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
4.  ROLES AND THE 1,000‑CALL PERSONAL API QUOTA
--------------------------------------------------------------------
• Viewer ............  read‑only, 1,000 calls/day
• Data Entry ........  can edit non‑cert sections, 1,000 calls/day
• Entity Administrator  full control, 1,000 calls/day
• No entity role ....  personal key limited to 10 calls/day

A Viewer role is sufficient for harvesting notice data and IVL rosters.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
5.  APPLY FOR A  SYSTEM ACCOUNT  (NON‑FEDERAL)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Purpose: returns IVL contact e‑mail/phone and provides a single
shared credential for your application.  Daily quota is 1,000
calls/day; higher tiers require a federal sponsor.

Step‑by‑step:
 1. Workspace ➜ System Accounts ➜ New Account.
 2. Tab  “System Info”
      – System Account Name
      – Interfacing System Name / Version
      – Two‑sentence business justification
 3. Tab  “Organization”
      – Select your UEI
      – Add an  “Other System Account Holder”  (backup user)
 4. Tab  “Permissions”
      – Tick  Contract Opportunities  ►  Public Read
        (Non‑federal accounts cannot request FOUO data)
 5. Tab  “Security”
      – List every outbound PUBLIC IP address or CIDR block
      – Connection type:  REST API
      – Server physical location
      – Security POC name & e‑mail
 6. Tab  “Authorization”  (optional for non‑federal) — upload any
      internal security docs if required by your org; otherwise skip.
 7. Review ➜ Submit ➜ accept Terms of Use.  An e‑mail one‑time code
      confirms your identity.
 8. Status flows  Draft ➜ Pending Review ➜ Published.
      Typical turnaround: 1–3 weeks.
 9. When status shows  Published, open the account and click
      “Generate API Key”.  Set the system‑account password.
      Rotate both every 90 days; SAM will send reminder e‑mails.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
6.  WHICH CREDENTIAL FOR WHICH TASK?
--------------------------------------------------------------------
• Search notices, pull IVL roster (no contact e‑mails) ...... Personal key
• Download nightly Entity Registration Public V2 extract .... Personal key
• Pull IVL roster WITH e‑mail & phone ........................ System Account
• Shared application credential or >1,000 calls/day quota ... System Account

--------------------------------------------------------------------
END OF QUICK‑START
